# Project Structure

The project contains five components — `simulation`, `ros2_stack`, `meshroom`, `gauss_splat`, and `vla_x3plus`:

```
simulation/
  environment.yml        # conda env definition (Python 3.12)
  simulation_setup.sh    # installs system deps + conda env + Isaac Sim 6.0.0
  config.yml             # simulation parameters
  src/                   # source code

ros2_stack/
  ros2_stack_setup.sh  # installs ROS 2 Jazzy + builds colcon workspace
  config.yml         # pick-and-place parameters
  ws/                # ROS 2 colcon workspace
    src/
      panda_pick_place/   # custom ROS 2 Python package
      topic_based_ros2_control/  # cloned at setup time (gitignored)

meshroom/
  meshroom_setup.sh  # downloads + verifies Meshroom binary
  config.yml         # reconstruction pipeline parameters + version
  src/               # source code (reconstruct.py wrapper)
  input/             # place image sets here (gitignored)
  output/            # reconstruction results (gitignored)
  Meshroom-<version>/ # prebuilt binary (Zenodo, gitignored)

gauss_splat/
  environment.yml        # conda env definition (Python 3.11)
  gauss_splat_setup.sh   # installs COLMAP + conda env + PyTorch + nerfstudio
  config.yml         # reconstruction parameters
  src/               # source code (reconstruct.py wrapper)
  input/             # place image sets here (gitignored)
  output/            # reconstruction results (gitignored)

vla_x3plus/
  environment.yml        # conda env definition (Python 3.10)
  vla_x3plus_setup.sh   # installs conda env + JAX, MuJoCo, Octo VLA
  config.yml         # model + simulation parameters
  src/               # source code (pick_and_place.py demo)
  urdf/              # x3plus URDF (reference copy from monty_isaac)
  models/            # MuJoCo MJCF scene (x3plus_mujoco.xml)
  third_party/octo/  # cloned Octo repo (gitignored)
  output/            # demo videos (gitignored)
```

## Cloning Private Repos

- Load `GH_TOKEN` from `.env` and use it for authenticated HTTPS clones: `git clone https://$GH_TOKEN@github.com/OWNER/REPO.git`.

## Dependency Placement

- Components with a conda env (e.g. `simulation`, `gauss_splat`, `vla_x3plus`): add Python/pip/conda deps to that component's `environment.yml`.
- Components without a conda env (e.g. `ros2_stack`, `meshroom`) and system-level packages: add deps to `common_setup.sh` or the component's `{name}_setup.sh`.

## Simulation Component

- Isaac Sim 6.0.0 and system deps are installed via `simulation/simulation_setup.sh`.
- Run standalone pick-and-place: `source activate_env.sh simulation && python -m src.pick_and_place`.
- Run ROS2-bridged scene: `source activate_env.sh simulation && python -m src.ros2_pick_and_place`.

## ROS2 Stack Component

- No conda env — uses native Ubuntu ROS 2 Jazzy packages.
- ROS 2, ros2_control, MoveIt2, BehaviorTree.CPP installed via `ros2_stack/ros2_stack_setup.sh`.
- `topic_based_ros2_control` is cloned and built in the colcon workspace.
- Uses MoveIt2 for motion planning, py_trees for BT orchestration.
- Run: `source activate_env.sh ros2_stack && ros2 launch panda_pick_place pick_place.launch.py`.

## Meshroom Component

- No conda env — uses prebuilt Meshroom (CUDA 12; version in `meshroom/config.yml`, URL auto-resolved from GitHub release).
- Default pipeline `photogrammetryObject` uses Grounding DINO + SAM for object detection/segmentation before reconstruction.
- `reconstruct.py` wraps `meshroom_batch` with a dual interface (function + CLI).
- Pass `--prompt "description"` to specify the target object; defaults to the object name.
- Other components call it via subprocess to maintain environment isolation.
- Reconstruct: `source activate_env.sh meshroom && python -m src.reconstruct --name <object> --prompt "description"`.
- Import into Isaac Sim: `source activate_env.sh simulation && python -m src.import_mesh --name <object>`.

## Gauss Splat Component

- Uses conda env (`roboex-gauss-splat`, Python 3.11) + nerfstudio (installed via `gauss_splat/gauss_splat_setup.sh`).
- COLMAP installed as system package by `gauss_splat/gauss_splat_setup.sh`.
- Pipeline: COLMAP SfM → splatfacto training → TSDF mesh extraction.
- Pass `--prompt "description"` to enable GDINO + SAM2 object segmentation before reconstruction.
  SAM2 video tracking propagates masks across all frames for temporally consistent results.
- Multi-view input (10-50 images) or video; ~5-15 min total vs 30-60 for Meshroom.
- Full-scene reconstruct: `source activate_env.sh gauss_splat && python -m src.reconstruct --name <object>`.
- Object-only reconstruct: `source activate_env.sh gauss_splat && python -m src.reconstruct --name <object> --prompt "description"`.
- Segment only: `source activate_env.sh gauss_splat && python -m src.segment --name <object> --prompt "description"`.
- Import into Isaac Sim: `source activate_env.sh simulation && python -m src.import_mesh --name <object> --source gauss_splat`.

## VLA X3Plus Component

- Uses conda env (`roboex-vla-x3plus`, Python 3.10) + Octo VLA + MuJoCo.
- Octo (octo-models/octo) is cloned into `third_party/octo/` by `vla_x3plus/vla_x3plus_setup.sh`.
- MuJoCo scene (`models/x3plus_mujoco.xml`) uses primitive geometry derived from the x3plus URDF kinematic chain.
- Original URDF kept in `urdf/` for reference; the arm has 5-DOF + parallel gripper (6 actuators).
- Run demo (with Octo): `source activate_env.sh vla_x3plus && python -m src.pick_and_place`.
- Run demo (random actions, no GPU): `source activate_env.sh vla_x3plus && python -m src.pick_and_place --random`.

## Running the ROS2 Pick-and-Place Demo

Terminal 1 (Isaac Sim): `source activate_env.sh simulation && python -m src.ros2_pick_and_place`
Terminal 2 (ROS2):      `source activate_env.sh ros2_stack && ros2 launch panda_pick_place pick_place.launch.py`
